SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 808
By Hatcher
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Blount County Mayor Ed
Mitchell on the occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm
throughout their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Ed Mitchell is one such estimable individual, who has served the citizens of
Blount County with distinction, including four consecutive terms as Blount County Mayor from
2010 until the conclusion of his current term in 2026; and
WHEREAS, a passionate sixth-generation Blount Countian, Mayor Mitchell continues to
reside on his family's farm, first settled in 1800 by his great-great-great-grandfather, reflecting a
deep and abiding connection to the land and the people he has long served; and
WHEREAS, Ed Mitchell is a graduate of Everett High School, Class of 1972, and
Tusculum College, where he earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Organizational
Management; and
WHEREAS, prior to his service as county mayor, Mayor Mitchell devoted thirty-two years
to public service in Blount County, including four and one-half years with the Blount County
Sheriff's Department and twenty-seven years with the Maryville Fire Department, where he
served six years as fire marshal and fifteen years as fire chief; and
WHEREAS, following a brief retirement devoted to farming Black Angus cattle, Ed
Mitchell was elected Blount County Mayor and was subsequently reelected in 2014, 2018, and
2022, providing steady leadership and continuity through four election cycles; and
WHEREAS, during Mayor Mitchell's tenure, Blount County has experienced a
remarkable financial transformation, reducing county debt from $238 million to an anticipated
$87 million by June 2026, increasing the fund balance from $9 million to $63 million, and
SJR0808
013211
- 1 -

improving net assets from a negative $75 million to $154 million, all while maintaining balanced
budgets each year; and
WHEREAS, under his leadership, Blount County achieved a AAA credit rating,
completed multiple consecutive clean audits, maintained a tax rate below the certified rate, and
incurred no new debt while making substantial investments in education, public facilities, and
infrastructure; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Ed Mitchell oversaw the construction of a new high school, more
than $80 million in capital improvements to the county's other high schools, a $21 million
renovation of Eagleton Ballpark, and the execution of a lease agreement ensuring the long-term
viability of Blount Memorial Hospital; and
WHEREAS, he placed a strong emphasis on modernization and efficiency in county
government, launching an information technology modernization program in 2017 that included
fiber infrastructure, updated accounting systems, a new county website, and improved
communications systems; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Mitchell also fostered collaboration among county departments,
municipalities, and community partners, contributing to major business recruitment and
expansion efforts, regional fiber connectivity initiatives, and the development of a transition
center in partnership with the McNabb Center; and
WHEREAS, his commitment to public safety included the establishment of an
emergency medical responder certification program for the Blount County Sheriff's Office,
resulting in more than eighty deputies receiving emergency medical certification and saving
countless lives; and
WHEREAS, wholly dedicated to his community, Mayor Mitchell has served on numerous
boards and committees, including the Blount County Community Action Board, the American
Red Cross Board, Keep Blount Beautiful, the American Heart Association, the Homeland
Security District 2 Board, the Boys and Girls Club of Blount County, and the Empty Pantry
Board; he is a graduate of Leadership Blount, Class of 1998; and
- 2 - 013211

WHEREAS, he currently serves on the Economic Development Board of Blount County
and the Tellico Reservoir Development Agency, and he is a member of the Maryville Kiwanis
Club; and
WHEREAS, known for his open-door policy and servant's heart, Mayor Ed Mitchell has
remained accessible to the citizens of Blount County and is especially recognized for his annual
volunteer service during the holiday season, as he brings joy and goodwill to community events
throughout the county; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Mitchell is a fourth-generation member of Broadway United
Methodist Church, reflecting a deep and enduring family connection to his faith and community;
and
WHEREAS, Ed Mitchell enjoys the love and support he shares with his wife of forty-two
years, Kim Mitchell; he is the proud father of two sons, Josh and Jordan, and the loving
grandfather of Mason, Lily, and Ella; and
WHEREAS, a strong advocate for the citizens of Blount County, Mayor Mitchell has
compiled a singular record of success during his exemplary public service career, and he should
be specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Blount County Mayor Ed
Mitchell for his exemplary service to the people of Blount County and the State of Tennessee,
extending to him our sincere appreciation and best wishes upon the occasion of his retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
